                                p.recipie-subTitle.mb-1 Ingredients
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 12 cups Bulgur wheat
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 1 Kg flour 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 2 handfuls salt 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 1.5 Kg chopped onions 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 Sumac to taste 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 1 Kg cooked chickpea
                    .col-lg-6.col-sm-6.col-12.mx-0.px-2.px-lg-0.mb-4
                        .row.mx-0.h-100
                            .col-12.p-0.m-0.pt-2
                                p.recipie-subTitle.mb-1 What is "Zenkol"?
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0  "Zenkol" means the motion to form a ball. Across Lebanon, many recipes are referred to as zengol, but every village uses different ingredients. Some make them using lentils, others with pumpkins. Although the name is the same, the recipes and dishes are totally different.
                            .col-12.p-0.m-0.pt-2
                                p.recipie-subTitle.mb-1 Method
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 Wash and drain the bulgur wheat. Add flour and salt, mix and knead until homogenous.  
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 Form the dough into little balls (Zenkol) place in the fridge. 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 In a hot pot, place the onions with some olive oil until golden, pour boiling water and wait until the mixture simmers again.
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 Add the zenkol and the soaked summac. Wait until the water starts to boil. It will thicken.
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 Taste the Zenkol and sauce, adjust acidity with some more summac or a bit of Lemon Juice to taste. 
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 When the zenkolâ€™s texture resembles to gnocchi, they are good to go.
                                p.recipie-ingredient.pt-2.mb-0 Add the pre-cooked chickpeas, wait till they are hot and serve. 
                    .col-12.p-0.m-0.pt-2
                        p.recipie-Title.mb-1 Teta Sisi's Tips
                    .col-lg-8.col-sm-8.col-12.mx-0.px-2.px-lg-0.mb-5
                        .row.mx-0.h-100
